org.jsonschema2pojo

Interface GenerationConfig

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Arguments, DefaultGenerationConfig, Jsonschema2PojoMojo, Jsonschema2PojoTask

    public interface GenerationConfig
    Defines the configuration options for Java type generation, including source and target paths/packages and all behavioural options (e.g should builders be generated, should primitives be used, etc).

    Devs: add to this interface if you need to introduce a new config property.

    • Method Detail

      • isGenerateBuilders

        boolean isGenerateBuilders()
        Gets the 'generateBuilders' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to generate builder-style methods of the form withXxx(value) (that return this), alongside the standard, void-return setters.

      • isUsePrimitives

        boolean isUsePrimitives()
        Gets the 'usePrimitives' configuration option.
        Returns:
        whether to use primitives (long, double , boolean) instead of wrapper types where possible when generating bean properties (has the side-effect of making those properties non-null).

      • getSource

        Iterator<File> getSource()
        Gets the 'source' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The source file(s) or directory(ies) from which JSON Schema will be read.

      • getTargetDirectory

        File getTargetDirectory()
        Gets the 'targetDirectory' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The target directory into which generated types will be written (may or may not exist before types are written)

      • getTargetPackage

        String getTargetPackage()
        Gets the 'targetPackage' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The java package used for generated types.

      • getPropertyWordDelimiters

        char[] getPropertyWordDelimiters()
        Gets the 'propertyWordDelimiters' configuration option.
        Returns:
        an array of characters that should act as word delimiters when choosing java bean property names.

      • isUseLongIntegers

        boolean isUseLongIntegers()
        Gets the 'useLongIntegers' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use the java type long (or Long) instead of int (or Integer) when representing the JSON Schema type 'integer'.

      • isUseDoubleNumbers

        boolean isUseDoubleNumbers()
        Gets the 'useDoubleNumbers' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use the java type double (or Double) instead of float (or Float) when representing the JSON Schema type 'number'.

      • isIncludeHashcodeAndEquals

        boolean isIncludeHashcodeAndEquals()
        Gets the 'includeHashcodeAndEquals' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use include hashCode and equals methods in generated Java types.

      • isIncludeToString

        boolean isIncludeToString()
        Gets the 'includeToString' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use include a toString method in generated Java types.

      • getAnnotationStyle

        AnnotationStyle getAnnotationStyle()
        Gets the 'annotationStyle' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The style of annotations to use in the generated Java types.

        Supported values:

        • jackson1 (apply annotations from the Jackson 1.x library)
        • jackson2 (apply annotations from the Jackson 2.x library)
        • gson (apply annotations from the gson library)
        • none (apply no annotations at all)
        See Also:
        AnnotatorFactory

      • getCustomAnnotator

        Class<? extends Annotator> getCustomAnnotator()
        Gets the 'customAnnotator' configuration option.
        Returns:
        An annotator that will be used in addition to the one chosen by getAnnotationStyle()

      • isIncludeJsr303Annotations

        boolean isIncludeJsr303Annotations()
        Gets the 'includeJsr303Annotations' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to include JSR-303 annotations (for schema rules like minimum, maximum, etc) in generated Java types.

      • getSourceType

        SourceType getSourceType()
        Gets the 'sourceType' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The type of input documents that will be read

        Supported values:

        • jsonschema
        • json

      • isRemoveOldOutput

        boolean isRemoveOldOutput()
        Gets the 'removeOldOutput' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to empty the target directory before generation occurs, to clear out all source files that have been generated previously. Be warned, when activated this option will cause jsonschema2pojo to indiscriminately delete the entire contents of the target directory (all files and folders) before it begins generating sources.

      • getOutputEncoding

        String getOutputEncoding()
        Gets the 'outputEncoding' configuration option.
        Returns:
        The character encoding that should be used when writing the generated Java source files.

      • isUseJodaDates

        boolean isUseJodaDates()
        Gets the 'useJodaDates' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use DateTime instead of Date when adding date type fields to generated Java types.

      • isUseCommonsLang3

        boolean isUseCommonsLang3()
        Gets the 'useCommonsLang3' configuration option.
        Returns:
        Whether to use commons-lang 3.x imports instead of commons-lang 2.x imports when adding equals, hashCode and toString methods.

      • getFileFilter

        FileFilter getFileFilter()
        Gets the file filter used to isolate the schema mapping files in the source directories.
        Returns:
        the file filter use when scanning for schema files.
